   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women Motorcycle Riders</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Rwanda, early pregnancy has increased from 6.1% to 7.3%. Most of these women drop out of school, and they are jobless. They&apos;re not able to raise and cover their children and expenses. They go for prostitution and drug abuse as a response. SafeMotos Institute plans to economically empower 200single mothers and poor unemployed women in Rwanda by enabling them to work in a male-dominated industry, motorcycle taxi industry. It&apos;s a worthy career, as they earn $10/day as an income to live and save.</narrative>
  </description>
